Sadio Mane trained with Bayern Munich for the first time on Friday, following his summer switch from Liverpool Mane, 30, linked up with his new teammates at Bayern’s Säbener Straße base, two days after the record champions began pre-season training ahead of the 2022/23 campaign. Fellow new signings Ryan Gravenberch and Noussair Mazraoui were also put through their paces by head coach Julian Nagelsmann.   Amstel Malta Ultra hails Falcons’ win over Botswana     Dembele’s agent spotted at Inter     2022 WAFCON: DStv, GOtv to beam Nigeria, Burundi tie   Mane joined Bayern at the end of June after a prolific and decorated spell at Liverpool. He tallied 120 goals and 48 assists in 269 competitive appearances for Jürgen Klopp’s team, whilst winning – among others – the English Premier League and UEFA Champions League. The Senegal striker has signed a three-year deal and will wear the No.17 shirt at new club Bayern. He is expected to be involved in match action when the 31-time Bundesliga champions face DC United (July 20). and Pep Guardiola’s Manchester City (23 July) as part of their US summer tour. Mane will have the opportunity to make his competitive debut on 29 July, when Bayern travel to DFB Cup holders RB Leipzig in the 2022 Supercup. Bayern begin the defence of their Bundesliga title away to reigning UEFA Europa League champions Eintracht Frankfurt on 5 August. The Bavarian giants are bidding to land a record-extending 11th straight league crown.